k is larger than 0.9 in most cases. The FPR (false\npositive rate) for the tracking of the attacker is also high, larger than 0.9\nin all cases. We also argue that the attack can remain completely oblivious to\nthe user and the website, thus making it extremely difficult to thwart in\npractice.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Oct 2021 17:42:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-20"}
